!============================================================================!
! 
!                             Welcome to CP-VASP!
!
! CP-VASP is a patch to the Vienna Ab-Initio Simulation Package (VASP) 
! to enable DFT calculations under constant electrode potential. This 
! is essential for accurately simulating the electrochemical interface, 
! where the Fermi level is controlled by external electrode potential. 
! CP-VASP enables fixed-structure calculation, structural relaxation, 
! and molecular dynamics (MD) simulations under a given electrode potential.
!
! This is the patch file for CP-VASP version 2. This patch is intended to be
! applied to VASP version 6.3.2 with VASPsol++ already installed. To
! apply the patch, copy this patch file into the /src directory in your VASP
! folder and execute the following command:
!    patch -p0 < cp-vaspsol++.patch
!
! If you have any challenges installing and/or running CP-VASP, please let us
! know by posting your question in the Issues tab on our GitHub page:
!    https://github.com/yuanyue-liu-group/CP-VASP/issues
!
! This code was written by Zachary Levell*, Ruoyu Wang*, Saerom Yu*, Xunhua
! Zhao, and Yuanyue Liu. (* These authors contributed equally). If you use
! this code in your work, please cite the following papers:
!   •	Zhao, X.; Liu, Y. Origin of Selective Production of Hydrogen Peroxide 
!       by Electrochemical !Oxygen Reduction. Journal of the American Chemical 
!       Society 2021, 143 (25), 9423-9428.
!   •	Yu, S.; Levell, Z.; Jiang, Z.; Zhao, X.; Liu, Y. What Is the 
!       Rate-Limiting Step of Oxygen Reduction Reaction on Fe–N–C Catalysts? 
!       Journal of the American Chemical Society 2023, 145 (46), 25352-25356. 
!
